name: Pasar Senggol Gianyar
address: Jl. Ngurah Rai-Gianyar No.38, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Fun time. Nice night market. Ate a lot of different food. Came through quickly the next day but may have been the coconut earlier or the extra heat I asked for. Either way a good experience at the night market that I will not forget.
review 2:
Brought here personally by my tour guide who needed to help us order food.
Had dinner here
Wide range of food available. From nasi to satay to desserts.
Local price. Very cheap and tasty. Per pax up to 15k for great portion. Possible to do some shopping at very low price.
review 3:
It is a traditional food and clothing market.
Mainly frequented by locals and with very few foreign visitors. Here you can taste real Indonesian food. I recommend the visit
review 4: Great night market full of good food and stuff to buy! Nice to be with locals only and not touristy restaurants
review 5: Largest night market we've been to in Bali. Came the times in a week and more stalls each time. Multiple srombotan stalls. Best one was in the corner with seating behind it.  All was for 5k. Satay of fish in the middle was quite nice but the pork belly was only ok. Lamb satay on the outside road was really nice. Ordered 20 by mistake but enjoyed it all. Boiled peanuts also available at the market.

name: Super Capital O 612 Dante Guesthouse
address: No.3, Jl. Hasanuddin No.I, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: Really good value for money. Centrally located near the Gianyar city center. The rooms and public areas are clean. The only reason I'm giving this review four stars is because the annoying front desk kept calling to remind me to vacate the room before 12. Called several times. I find that a bit intruding. When we confirm to check out before 12, that means we will.
review 2: Doesn‚Äôt feel clean. Had suspicion sheets weren‚Äôt freshly washed. Woke up itchy. Maybe bed bugs. At first air con didn‚Äôt work, but front desk guy fixed quick enough. Place smelled. It‚Äôs cheap but I think you‚Äôre better off paying a bit more to get better.
review 3:
The check-in time is 2pm and check-out before 12pm.
If you check-in early or check-out late, they will charged extra 30% to 50% the regular price (as I read on their policy at check-in desk).

The bedsheet and blanket were smelly and I spotted some blood stain on it.
At first I didn't notice and got itchy. I asked for changing and they changed the new set for us.

The room have bed light, TV, AC, closet, and clothes hanger, free wifi, a pool, and eating area. The room isn't soundproof, and they don't have scooter rental or laundry service.

The location is good to explore night market. Unfortunately we couldn't go see waterfall because of the heavy rain (it's July but there are raining a lot).

Gianyar doesn't have many activities so it's quite boring in my opinion.
review 4: Very dirty, linens looks like not been washed for a long time, the room is smelly and the bathroom is very dirty
review 5: Good room for the price. Wouldn‚Äôt have expected any more. The bathroom wasn‚Äôt super clean but okay. Very nice and helpful staff. Great location. Close to a few waterfalls like Kanto lampo.

name: Hotel Gianyar
address: Jl. Manik, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1:
200IDR no refrigerator, no kettle. Upgrade if you like, about 300IDR. Room No 50:

AC hasn‚Äôt been cleaned for years. Pillows has reached its end of life. Room is relatively clean. Doesn‚Äôt smell. Hot water and water pressure is good. Friendly staff. Just a few touch up should make this hotel good. Pillows and AC cleaning need urgent attention.

Sheets aren‚Äôt changed after every guest. This is shocking but almost standard practice in Indonesia.
review 2: Definitely won't visit it again. Ceiling got hole, wood cupboard got moles, sink was broken. The worst it's creepy and horror, overall an eerie experience. A no-no for a scaredy cat like me! ü§£
review 3: It's cheap and moat of the facilities are worth the prize. They have hot shower, and it works all the time. They have bathtub and big enough to snuggle in and relax your shoulder. But there may be times where the duppa (?) Smells really strong. But it's a culture there, so that's okay.
review 4:
High value for the price.
Friendly and helpful staff.
Good location in the center of Gianyar and still very quiet.
review 5: Lovely service for such a cheap price... Very friendly staff.. Great washing service. Can see mount Agung from one room block. Great food and grounds. Easy access to town and shops.

name: Taman Kota Ciung Wanara Gianyar
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara-Gianyar No.1, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: This city become one of the beautiful city in Bali Island, after the Head of the city restructured some of the spaces in this place, like the streets light and garden of the city, if you visit or passing by to the center City of Gianyar, especially in the night you will find the difference before and after they did it, the street lights it so beautiful, look like they will have big ceremony,because the lights similar with the Penjor what they put and use surround the street during ceremony like Galungan And Kuningan Day, thank you so much to the Head of Gianyar City, Bali. Now this city become iconic in the region of Gianyar.
review 2: Cute, small but cozy and clean in the middle of the town. We can see traffic but safe.
review 3:
A cozy place to spend your time by watching a light-programmed fountain.
Unfortunately, it's hard to find dustbins around this place.
review 4: Good place for relax after jogging around. Can seat on the bench there

name: BELIKOPI. GIANYAR BALI
address: Jl. Dharma Giri No.9, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: Best proletarian coffee cafe with satisfying free wifi..
review 2: Great relaxing place.  We only stopped in for a quick coffee but lazed around for a hour or so.  Staff were friendly and coffee was superb

name: Warmmeet Gianyar
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara-Gianyar No.88, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Great place to do your work from cafe or meetings (the name stands for itself). With a quiet and spacious area indoor or outdoor accompanied with a decent food & beverages.
review 2: The first coffee shop I visited in Gianyar, strategic location and easy to find. Cozy place and the coffee is good so you can hang out with friends or partners.
review 3:
Here only to get quick coffee, but it beyond perfect! i dont expect much but this coffee shop is sensational

they have selection of yummy pastries! and an offer as well in specific hour.
the parking lot is enough, the service is amazing as their staff is super friendly.

many instagramable spot right there.
highly recommend!üíØ
review 4:
Everything was great here. The place was comfy, lot of plug for charge, good for working, wifi was fast tho!!
Coffee taste great i drink ice latte perfect balance espresso with milk!! The ramen was very flavor!! Nothing wrong whit this place love it.
review 5: Not easy to find an air conditioned caf√© in Gianyar. Good quality coffee and warm dishes, but the place was noisy and with a bad echo. Not conducive for co-working at all! It needs some more furniture and decoration - it feels like a waiting room at a bus terminal.

name: Burger Bangor Gianyar
address: Jl. Dharma Giri No.9, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Bali, 80511, Indonesia
review 1: A local burger üçî chain - cheap price flavor is okay. The staffs are friendly- I asked before ordering because we were just in the area - since I saw all the 1star review - so I was anticipated about bad experience or long waiting but no long wait - bought package 6 all include drinks. Mosty its for take away but we ate there.
review 2: delicious burger but the bad service must be improved! I waited for 1 burger more than 25 minutes! employees can't work especially those two men! bad üëé
review 3: Waiting for food for over 1 hour, the food keeps getting delayed, unsure if it will arrive at all after paying
review 4: Staff not nice they must learn from bangor sesetan how to service customers
review 5: Incompetent people running this place. Very dirty dining area. Poorly managed!

name: Ejji Coffee Dharmagiri Gianyar District 24
address: Jl. Dharma Giri No.18c, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: Best place to have sweet drinks and pastries while chilling, enjoying your time alone. The place has good wi-fi, a relaxing atmosphere, and also really clean and simple with Japanese vibes.
review 2:
good taste with a great ambianceü´∂
ejji coffee is a must try
review 3: Nice place, the ambience good to do some short work and chilling. The indoor space quite large for small coffee shop and they also have small outdoor sitting. The coffee quality is decent for me. The parking space is small tough
review 4: A proper coffee shop in gianyar area. Clean, humble and of course a good coffee‚Ä¶

review 1: Best Chicken Porridge in Gianyar, humble and friendliy seller...taste great!
review 2: Best breakfast porridge around.  Opens very early, maybe 4am. While you can get sweet, the variety of toppings is wonderful.
review 3: Very tasty bubur. Opens very early, about 4am I think. The juice also excellent.
review 4: The taste is good, i like also ^sate usus^ . The location in the area of traditional market.

name: Lee Salad x Seblak Ndug Gianyar
address: Jl. Raden Wijaya No.102, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia

name: Warung Babi Guling Pande Oka
address: Jl. Jata No.1, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1:
One of the best babi guling in Bali, i have known. the have been selling babi guling for genereations and really authentic.
Price a little expensive than other,but it worth to try
review 2: Located close to the Pasar Umum Gianyar, there are actually a lot of choices place to eat in the area. The price is quite pricey (40k with drink) and the size for one portion is big enough. For local, the taste is flat but it's okay to try if you want to know the taste of Babi Guling.
review 3: great place to try Bali's Babi Guling. it's a family run Warung. for tourists, this is a bit off of the usual spots, but is as cheap and as delicious as they come. that cripy pig skin... üòçüòå a true heart stopper, figuratively and literally. üòÇ
review 4: It's good, nice & clean.. if you are looking for Balinese suckling pig - Gianyar province style, you should go here.. the skin is crispy
review 5:
Full regrets!

As I have to agreed to a friend recommendation so called the famous babi guling in Gianyar area and we decided to have a lunch break which I don‚Äôt feel so exciting at the first impression üôÑ

I have Never been to a culinary place that left me so dislike and regret!

Food taste 4/10, the sambal way too salty to my palate

Price was un-fair as they charged 40k per portion/per person,  while others local were charge for 20k per portion, it wasn‚Äôt happy Experience for us!
and for you to know, we are local people too! Whom Residing in Bali

Lastly,
personally it wasn‚Äôt value for money and the place is dirty too!

review 1: The food is great and tasty. The service is also excellent. Have no complaints about it.
review 2: I got sick from bad pineapple juice in my pineapple crush.  The beef pepperoni pizza has no tomato sauce on it.
review 3:
Pizza and salad were awesome.

name: Run Run. Gianyar

name: Warung Pande Babi Guling
address: Jl. Kebo Iwa No.99x, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1:
Pretty good babi guling restaurant near Gianyar downtown. Ordered just one babi guling and bottle of water and paid just 45k.

was super cheap! and the taste was much better than famous babi guling restaurant like Babi guling Ibu Oka

The pork skin was tender and the soup with a pork and radish had a nice flavor.  recommended if you're visiting Gianyar and finding something for good lunch!
review 2: It was the first time I visited this place because it was a bit too far from Denpasar. I like the place, the taste and the price. Good thing that I didn't have to wait for a long line.
review 3:
they have special and complete
special without pork skin
complete with the crunchy pork skin
for the beverage, i like the orange orange without sugar so refreshing!
review 4: At first it seems unassuming place for babi guling, I actually get lost the first time I try to get here because the one way street. After that I went in and ordered a plate of babi guling, when the food came to my table, I try the skin and after that wondering why tourists haven‚Äôt come here to eat. Easily the best babi guling in Gianyar

review 1: Delicious...for the prices standard.....placed at noon very busy so delivery order more better
review 2: goid taste, but i think the fish is too small

name: Mr.Crip's
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara-Gianyar No.10, Gianyar, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80511, Indonesia
review 1: awesome food, cheap, good service, I will give 5 stars if they serve regular ice tea instead of only ice lemon tea
review 2: My girlfriend went there last week on a trip from Singapore, she ordered a simple meal; fried chicken with fries and hot lemon tea. Hours later in the night she had intense stomach pains followed by severe vomiting, she had to cut her trip short because of this. I didn't get the chance to deal with the matter myself since I wasn't present on this trip but I'm writing this to warn others about this place, I wouldn't want anyone else to be a victim.
review 3:
It's the hanging out place for junior high and high school students of Gianyar who are looking for standard food and free wifi. The food is a bit more expensive to other fried chicken outlet. Thera are also some half hearted experiment to expand the menu like pizza, noodle, kwetiau, chicken steak, but all of that don't taste and look well thought out.
Well, since most of their customer don't really pay attention to their food, they got by so far.
review 5: Easy to get there. The foods are delicious. There are many variant of food. Good services by the waitress.

very cheap

review 2: Delicious, friedly price.  Middle javanese taste

review 4:
The soto isn't good at all for my taste.

Too much mirror all over the wall of restaurant, kind of ruining everything even more.
review 5: Excellent fried chicken.  Sambal pedas is quite hot for the expat, but if you have acquired a taste for the local heat, then you will love it.  If your not sure, just try a little. But beware.
